</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C314651FFFF9FFBCFF02FE92FE985492" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB13694FFF9FFBCFF02FE92FE985492" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,500]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">
<emphasis id="B97AEA86FFF9FFBCFF02FE92FE835426" bold="true" box="[199,308,295,320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Remarks</emphasis>
. One morphological characteristic is unusual: a bare metasternum. This character state is not common in this genus, and it is only found otherwise in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D17FFF9FFBCFCFFFEF8FAED5403" authority="Vockeroth, 1969" authorityName="Vockeroth" authorityYear="1969" box="[826,1370,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadricornutum">
<emphasis id="B97AEA86FFF9FFBCFCFFFEF8FB245403" box="[826,1171,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Citrogramma quadricornutum</emphasis>
Vockeroth, 
<number id="3DC624B3FFF9FFBCFAE7FEF9FAED5403" box="[1314,1370,332,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" value="1969.0">1969</number>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F3197604FFF9FFBCFF52FEC5FECC54EE" box="[151,379,367,392]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
. The interesting fact is that the 
<typeStatus id="54B58836FFF9FFBCFD3CFEDAFCEC54EE" box="[761,859,367,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">holotype</typeStatus>
male has a pilose metasternum (Mengual 
<number id="3DC624B3FFF9FFBCFA91FEC5FA2754EE" box="[1364,1424,368,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" value="2012.0">2012</number>
), suggesting that the pili of the metasternum of these females were rubbed off in the Malaise trap, or during mounting. Mengual (
<number id="3DC624B3FFF9FFBCFE56FE0DFE6654B6" box="[403,465,440,464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" value="2012.0">2012</number>
: 
<number id="3DC624B3FFF9FFBCFE26FE0DFDB954B6" box="[483,526,440,464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" value="132.0">132</number>
) found a female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D17FFF9FFBCFCD1FE0DFB7354B6" authority="Ghorpade, 1994" authorityName="Ghorpade" authorityYear="1994" box="[788,1220,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chola">
<emphasis id="B97AEA86FFF9FFBCFCD1FE0DFC4F54B6" box="[788,1016,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="391">Citrogramma chola</emphasis>
Ghorpadé, 
<number id="3DC624B3FFF9FFBCFB49FE0DFB7354B6" box="[1164,1220,440,464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="391" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</taxonomicName>
also with a bare metasternum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
